cache.set("userId_101", { name: "Aria" });
cache.set({ tempId: 1 }, "Active");

console.log(cache.size); // 2
console.log(cache.has("userId_101")); // true`,exercises:[{id:"map-frequency-counter",title:"Deduplicated Frequency Counter Map",difficulty:"DSA Easy",conceptContext:"Instead of standard objects, using `new Map()` allows storing count records safely. We check existence with `map.has(key)` and retrieve counts with `map.get(key)`.",description:"Let's build a clean item occurrences tally using Map collections! How it works In real-world data telemetry, counting high-speed sensor inputs or indexing client session requests requires highly optimized hash maps with minimal prototype pollution risk.\n\nWrite a function `frequencyMap(arr)` that loops through an array, computes the count of each item, and returns a native ES6 `Map` object mapping items to their frequencies.",codeTemplate:`function frequencyMap(arr) {
